- **API key management** — **`ApiKeyService`** / **`modules/api-keys/`**; generate **`1cmd_{64-hex}`**; store **`key_prefix`** (first **12** chars) + **SHA-256** **`key_hash`** only; scope to **org** + optional **`account_id`**; **`permissions`** (`resource:action:scope`); **`rate_limit`**; optional **`expires_at`**; org admin JWT **`GET/POST /api/v1/api-keys`**, **`GET/PATCH/DELETE /api/v1/api-keys/:id`**, **`POST …/:id/rotate`**; plaintext secret **only** on **create** / **rotate**; **revoke** → **`is_active: false`**; machine auth **`X-API-Key`** or **`Authorization: Bearer 1cmd_…`** — **`createApiKeyAuthMiddleware`**				
- **Hierarchy REST**: `/organizations` (platform admin bearer `PLATFORM_ADMIN_TOKEN`); **`/accounts`**, **`/departments`**, **`/users`** require **`Authorization: Bearer <access JWT>`** with **`org_id`** claim → **`tenantMiddleware`** sets **`req.tenantId`** (reject mismatched `org_id` query); minimum **`role`** from JWT claim (legacy **`X-User-Role`** header fallback)				
				
## BASE SCHEMA (Every MongoDB Collection)				
{				
  org_id: ObjectId,        // REQUIRED - tenant isolation				
  account_id?: ObjectId,   // For account-scoped resources				
  department_id?: ObjectId,// For dept-scoped resources				
  created_by: ObjectId,				
  created_at: Date,				
  updated_by: ObjectId,				
  updated_at: Date,				
  is_deleted: boolean,				
  _version: number				
}				
				
## SECURITY RULES (NEVER VIOLATE)				
1. org_id from JWT, NEVER from request body				
2. ALL queries include { org_id: req.tenantId, is_deleted: false }				
3. Audit log ALL mutations				
4. Validate ALL inputs with **Joi/Zod** — **`validation.middleware.ts`** (`validate`, `validateZodBody` / `Query` / `Params`); **400** `{ error: "Validation Error", details: [{ field, message }] }`; **`stripUnknown: true`**, **`abortEarly: false`**; route-level validators in **`*.validation.ts`**; OpenAPI **`#/components/responses/ValidationError`**; **`docs/REQUEST-VALIDATION.md`**				
5. **Field-level encryption** — **AES-256-GCM** for **PII**, **credentials**, **secrets** at rest (`@common/encryption/field-encryption.ts`, **`FIELD_ENCRYPTION_KEY`** 64-hex from **HashiCorp Vault** KV); **key management** — **Vault** transit + **AWS KMS** app CMK (`modules/kms-app-encryption`), **key rotation** (KMS annual, Vault transit + quarterly `FIELD_ENCRYPTION_KEY`), **access audit** (Vault audit device, **CloudTrail** `kms:*`); policies **`infrastructure/vault/policies/`**, runbook **`docs/runbooks/key-management.md`**; **Mongoose plugin** (`mongoose-field-encryption.plugin.ts`) on **User** (`phone_number`, `ssn`, TOTP), **Organization** (OIDC `client_secret`, SAML SP key), **Connector** (`credentials`); **searchable encryption** via HMAC blind indexes (`phone_number_search`, `ssn_search`) for exact lookup; **API keys** use **SHA-256 hash** only (not reversible); **`docs/FIELD-ENCRYPTION.md`**
6. **Encryption at rest** on all databases and object storage — **AES-256**, **CMK** via AWS KMS where supported; see **`docs/runbooks/encryption-at-rest.md`**
7. **Encryption in transit** — **TLS 1.3** API, **TLS** to all data stores, **Istio mTLS** between services; **no plaintext** in staging/production; see **`docs/runbooks/encryption-in-transit.md`**
8. **Key management** — **HashiCorp Vault** or **AWS KMS**; **key rotation** + **access audit**; never commit `FIELD_ENCRYPTION_KEY`; see **`docs/runbooks/key-management.md`**				
				
## CODE STANDARDS				
- TypeScript strict mode, no any				
- Dependency injection via InversifyJS				
- OpenAPI spec for all endpoints (**`swagger-jsdoc`** + **`swagger-ui-express`**; **`GET /api/docs`**, **`GET /api/docs/json`**; optional **`openapi-typescript`** types)				
- **Jest** for **unit**, **Supertest** for **integration**, **Playwright** for **E2E**; **80%** coverage threshold in CI				
- ESLint + Prettier enforced				
				
